      "writtenOn": "2015-12-28T18:57:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I find this behavior most confusing than helpful -- as a user, when I call a function that encodes argument, I\u0027m prepared for a char turning into a string after encoding. It\u0027s wrong to make assumptions about string length, and a comment to that effect on the API functions suffices.\n\nOTOH, arbitrarily disabling an already somewhat arbitrary format string syntax is confusing, IMO.",
