      "writtenOn": "2015-12-28T21:20:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You might be prepared, but the format string is different for char and String - %c/%s. It\u0027s very non-obvious to the reader if one passes char into the argument list with a corresponding %s format specifier. It\u0027s also very error-prone as most people would just write %c there without even thinking\nSo I really prefer the safest case - disable it. If you really need a char, just explicitly pass temporary string there - both String and std::string have shrot-string optimization which makes 1-char string very cheap",
